	<hr width="85%" />

	<table width="85%" cellspacing="3" cellpadding="0" border="0" align="center">
	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Author:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>blargg</b> [ Wed Nov 28, 2012 1:39 pm ]</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>Re: How many milliamps on the +5vDC line?</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />In addition to the NES mainboard, the power adapter supplies power to the bridge rectifier and regulator, both of which use (waste) a significant amount of power.<br /><br />The regulator also likely has plenty of spare capacity for powering more things, and it and the power adapter can be pushed beyond their specs, so that doesn't give us much of an idea of how much the mainboard uses.<br /><br />These distinctions are why I'm curious as to the motivation behind the original question, what the poster plans on doing with this information.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


	<hr width="85%" />

	<table width="85%" cellspacing="3" cellpadding="0" border="0" align="center">
